body:
Hi, while upgrading to v5.016, I get the internal error below when trying to use the streaming operator on a packed struct. This worked in prior versions.
```
%Error: Internal Error: verilator_test_tb.sv:11:43: ../V3AstNodeDType.h:1133: call isCompound on subdata type, not reference
   11 |   function automatic logic [63:0] reverse(data_t d);
      |                                           ^~~~~~
```
Example to reproduce:
```
`default_nettype none
module verilator_test_tb (
  input wire [63:0] data_i,
  output logic [63:0] data_o
);

  typedef struct packed {
    logic [63:0] dummy;
  } data_t;

  function automatic logic [63:0] reverse(data_t d);
    return {<<{d}};
  endfunction

  assign data_o = reverse(data_i);

endmodule
`default_nettype wire
```
I found a work-around by adding a cast:
```
  function automatic logic [63:0] reverse(data_t d);
    return {<<{$bits(d)'(d)}};
  endfunction
```
Verilator version:
```
% verilator --version
Verilator 5.016 2023-09-16 rev UNKNOWN.REV
```
